==German==
===Etymology 1===
From Proto-Germanic ''*ainlif-'' (''eleven''), a compound of ''*ainaz'' (''one'') and ''*lif-''.
====Noun====
'''Elf''' (''all singular cases:'' '''Elf''', ''not used in plural'')
# A [[football]] [[team]] (so called because that is the number of players on such a team).

===Etymology 2===
From Indo-European root ''albho-'' (''brilliant, shining white'').
====Noun====
'''Elf''' ''m'' (''genitive singular:'' '''[[Elfen]]''', ''nominative plural:'' '''[[Elfen]]''')
# [[elf#English|Elf]].
